{"cursor":"22853","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = National Institute of Allergy and\nInfectious Diseases |nativename = NIAID |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo =\nUS-NIH-NIAID-Logo.svg |logo_width = 140px |logo_caption = NIAID logo |seal =\n|seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = 1955 |date1 = |date1_name = |date2 =\n|date2_name = |preceding1 =National Microbiological Institute |preceding2 =\n|dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = Bethesda, Maryland\n|chief1_name = Anthony S. Fauci |chief1_position = Director |parent_agency =\nNational Institutes of Health |website = }} The 'National Institute of Allergy\nand Infectious Diseases' ('NIAID') is one of the 27 institutes and centers that\nmake up the National Institutes of Health (NIH), an agency of the United States\nDepartment of Health and Human Services (HHS). NIAID's mission is to conduct\nbasic and applied research to better understand, treat, and prevent infectious,\nimmunologic, and allergic diseases. [http://www.niaid.nih.gov/-\nabout/whoWeAre/Documents/fy09FactBook.pdf NIAID Fiscal Year 2009 Fact\nBook]\n\nNIAID has \"intramural\" (in-house) laboratories in Maryland and Montana, and\nfunds research conducted by scientists at institutions in the United States and\nthroughout the world. NIAID also works closely with partners in academia,\nindustry, government, and non-governmental organizations in multifaceted and\nmultidisciplinary efforts to address emerging health challenges such as the\npandemic H1N1/09 virus.\n","linknr":282,"url":"National_Institute_of_Allergy_and_Infectious_Diseases","recorded":1376415345,"links":["/w/index.php?title=National_Institute_of_Allergy_and_Infectious_Diseases&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=National_Institute_of_Allergy_and_Infectious_Diseases&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/lic